(firstQuint)Cervical Interlaminar Versus Transforaminal Epidural Steroid Injection.

 This study will compare one route of epidural steroid injection (interlaminar) using a particulate steroid to another route of epidural steroid injection (transforaminal) using a different non-particulate steroid dexamethasone.

 Repeat injections may be allowed.

 All injections will be done with image guidance.

 Patients will be evaluated for improvements in pain and function.

